                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12624868" author="alangates" created="Fri, 22 Aug 2008 15:28:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch changes the launcher classes to check for any failed jobs, instead of just checking that progress is 100% when hadoop declares all jobs finished.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12625215" author="olgan" created="Sun, 24 Aug 2008 19:11:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Alan, how do I validate the patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12625318" author="shravanmn" created="Mon, 25 Aug 2008 10:57:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;But the calculateProgress does the same thing. It returns the progress of all the jobs as (sum of all successful jobs and running progress of running jobs). The launchers know how many jobs were launched. If JobControl works correctly, the completion check to see that the progress returned by calculateProgress equals num MR jobs submitted is right. Can you give me a sample script where it was failing?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12625545" author="olgan" created="Mon, 25 Aug 2008 23:22:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch committed. thanks, Alan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
